./

apstack__define.pro


This class is an object-oriented wrapper around a basic stack. The undelying structure is an array. Values are added to the beginning and popped from the beginning.

apStack::push, var [, /TO_END]

Pushes a value to the beginning of the stack

Parameters

var required

The value being pushed onto the stack

Keywords

TO_END optional type=boolean

Set this keyword to push the value onto the end of the stack (pushing to the beginning is the default behavior).
